WEBVTT

00:02.250 --> 00:03.920
DHS is holding a group of people
against their will in a camp.

00:03.920 --> 00:05.620
Don't jump
into a volcano again.

00:05.620 --> 00:07.120
Previously on "The Crossing"...

00:07.120 --> 00:08.290
[ Gunshot ]

00:08.290 --> 00:09.620
There's
a federal agent missing.

00:09.620 --> 00:13.080
I think her superior, Lindauer,
had something to do with it.

00:13.080 --> 00:14.040
He's some sort of prodigy.

00:14.040 --> 00:15.040
Scary smart.

00:15.040 --> 00:16.290
Almost like he could --

00:16.290 --> 00:17.750
Tell the future.

00:17.750 --> 00:19.750
Oh.
Look what I found.

00:19.750 --> 00:22.040
With the serial number
shaved off.

00:22.040 --> 00:23.750
This really the play
you want to make, Sheriff?

00:23.750 --> 00:25.250
Get your ass in the car.

00:25.250 --> 00:26.420
Let's go.

00:26.420 --> 00:28.380
I found this rash
on her neck.

00:28.380 --> 00:29.460
Dr. Fleischer:
It's not even a rash.

00:29.460 --> 00:30.960
I think it's a brand.

00:30.960 --> 00:32.290
She's been branded.

00:32.290 --> 00:34.290
Hannah:
I was meant to find you.

00:34.290 --> 00:36.330
They said if I found you
I'd be okay.

00:36.330 --> 00:37.880
Rebecca:
Leah is completely healed.

00:37.880 --> 00:39.120
Leah's mother.

00:39.120 --> 00:40.790
She's here, isn't she?

00:40.790 --> 00:41.880
Apex.

00:41.880 --> 00:45.040
You can't trust them.

00:45.040 --> 00:48.750
♪♪

00:48.750 --> 00:50.880
Aren't you
forgetting someone?

00:52.670 --> 00:54.460
-Mister Hops!
-[ Laughs ]

00:54.460 --> 00:57.120
That was close.
You ready to go?

00:57.120 --> 00:58.960
I don't want to see either one
of you back here again, okay?

00:58.960 --> 01:00.330
Okay.

01:00.330 --> 01:02.670
Oh, we wanted to say goodbye
to Dr. Forbin.

01:02.670 --> 01:04.080
You and me both.

01:04.080 --> 01:07.290
Apparently she's already
moved on to another assignment.

01:07.290 --> 01:10.040
Oh, uh, too bad.

01:10.040 --> 01:11.830
Bye, Nurse Lindsay.

01:11.830 --> 01:13.380
Bye, sweetheart.

01:13.380 --> 01:15.540
[ Coughing ]
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

01:15.540 --> 01:17.960
Get Dr. Fleischer, please.
I need him immediately.

01:17.960 --> 01:20.420
[ Coughing continues ]

01:20.420 --> 01:22.620
We weren't sure
you were ever gonna wake up.

01:22.620 --> 01:23.620
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:23.620 --> 01:25.750
Here.
Okay.

01:25.750 --> 01:27.830
Okay, easy.

01:27.830 --> 01:30.830
Easy. You haven't
had a sip in weeks.

01:30.830 --> 01:32.790
Okay, okay. Shh.

01:32.790 --> 01:34.670
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:34.670 --> 01:41.750
♪♪

01:41.750 --> 01:44.080
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:47.080 --> 01:49.210
Why are they all
staring at me?

01:51.710 --> 01:53.290
[ Sighs ]

01:53.290 --> 01:55.460
Everyone in the camp
loves someone

01:55.460 --> 01:57.460
who got sick
just like you did,

01:57.460 --> 02:01.790
but the people they love,
they didn't get better,

02:01.790 --> 02:05.170
so they're all just surprised
and happy to see you.

02:07.330 --> 02:09.330
Dr. Fleischer:
You've essentially been
asleep for two weeks.

02:09.330 --> 02:11.710
When you swallow as much
ocean water as you did,

02:11.710 --> 02:13.540
the sodium levels
in your blood spike.

02:13.540 --> 02:16.170
And that causes your brain
to swell, puts your lights out.

02:16.170 --> 02:17.880
So we hooked you up
to some IV fluid

02:17.880 --> 02:20.250
and gradually brought your
levels back down to normal.

02:20.250 --> 02:22.920
♪♪

02:22.920 --> 02:25.920
I don't want you talking
to anybody, do you understand?

02:28.670 --> 02:30.580
[ Explosion, people screaming ]

02:33.040 --> 02:36.120
Did a man named Eli
come here with the others?

02:38.170 --> 02:40.790
I'm sorry. Probably didn't
make it out the water.

02:42.830 --> 02:44.250
Good.

02:44.250 --> 02:47.460
♪♪

02:47.460 --> 02:49.170
I have work to do.

02:54.540 --> 02:58.920
♪♪

03:01.380 --> 03:06.080
♪♪

03:06.080 --> 03:07.790
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

03:12.080 --> 03:13.920
Thank you.
Yeah.

03:17.790 --> 03:19.210
This isn't half bad.

03:19.210 --> 03:20.710
Glad you think so.

03:20.710 --> 03:22.920
I look forward
to your Yelp review.

03:22.920 --> 03:27.040
Would've been five stars
but for the unlawful detainment.

03:27.040 --> 03:30.580
Well, I found a .9mm throwaway
in your glove box,

03:30.580 --> 03:33.460
and I like the brains inside
my head, so agree to disagree.

03:33.460 --> 03:35.080
As I might've mentioned,

03:35.080 --> 03:37.750
the gun belongs
to an ongoing investigation.

03:37.750 --> 03:39.540
Emma Ren --
What about that?

03:39.540 --> 03:41.620
Is that an ongoing
investigation?

03:41.620 --> 03:42.880
Unfortunately, yes.

03:42.880 --> 03:45.120
She's been missing
for several days.

03:45.120 --> 03:46.250
I don't know
what to think.

03:46.250 --> 03:48.120
I've been in touch
with her parents.

03:48.120 --> 03:50.580
She's their only child.
Don't do that.

03:50.580 --> 03:54.880
Don't waste my time doing an
impersonation of a human being.

03:54.880 --> 03:58.120
I don't entirely understand
your little game here, Sheriff,

03:58.120 --> 03:59.880
but please show
some decency.

03:59.880 --> 04:00.960
Emma is a friend.

04:00.960 --> 04:02.670
Does that
make it harder...

04:02.670 --> 04:05.250
being complicit
in her disappearance?

04:05.250 --> 04:09.000
[ Scoffs ]
You know, it's sad.

04:09.000 --> 04:12.460
This makes perfect sense coming
from a man in your position.

04:12.460 --> 04:15.170
Big-city cop melts down,
moves to a small town,

04:15.170 --> 04:17.000
but things
are too simple there,

04:17.000 --> 04:19.080
so he finds ways
to complicate them.

04:19.080 --> 04:21.460
You suffered trauma
in the line of duty.

04:21.460 --> 04:23.460
PTSD
is a foregone conclusion.

04:23.460 --> 04:25.500
You're an
active-duty sheriff

04:25.500 --> 04:28.250
presenting with paranoia
and delusions of persecution.

04:28.250 --> 04:31.080
Psychology Today subscriber.

04:31.080 --> 04:32.710
I knew it.

04:32.710 --> 04:35.250
I like it, too, all right?
I read it in the can.

04:35.250 --> 04:39.330
You need to get help before you
make a career-ending mistake.

04:41.290 --> 04:43.500
Taking out Emma
just doesn't fit

04:43.500 --> 04:46.250
your psychological profile,
does it?

04:46.250 --> 04:49.420
No, you're well-educated,
clean-cut, precise.

04:49.420 --> 04:52.250
Whatever happened to her,
it wasn't part of your plan.

04:52.250 --> 04:55.040
Of course, nothing is really
part of the plan lately, is it?

04:55.040 --> 04:57.040
There's something about
those 47 people

04:57.040 --> 04:58.880
that washed up
on that beach

04:58.880 --> 05:02.250
that put your world
into a tailspin.

05:02.250 --> 05:05.290
You realize you're conflating me
with your old sergeant.

05:05.290 --> 05:07.380
You think if you get your man
this time,

05:07.380 --> 05:09.420
it fixes the mistakes
of your past.

05:09.420 --> 05:11.460
It's a lot simpler
than that.

05:14.710 --> 05:16.880
I can't help myself.

05:18.670 --> 05:20.290
I will take you down.

05:21.420 --> 05:24.460
And if you try to
"permanent solution" me again

05:24.460 --> 05:27.460
or if I go missing,
everything I got on you

05:27.460 --> 05:31.210
goes straight to people that
demand answers for a living.

05:31.210 --> 05:33.830
What will they
be demanding answers to?

05:33.830 --> 05:36.620
Let's start with the earlier
migration 10 years ago.

05:36.620 --> 05:38.210
Why are you covering it up?

05:38.210 --> 05:40.380
Maybe it's because
you're using them,

05:40.380 --> 05:42.250
using their knowledge
of the future.

05:42.250 --> 05:45.000
Or maybe...

05:46.540 --> 05:47.670
Maybe what?

05:51.500 --> 05:53.330
Maybe you're one of them.

05:53.330 --> 05:55.380
[ Knock on door ]

05:55.380 --> 05:56.790
Mayor would like
to talk to you.

05:56.790 --> 05:58.210
Take a message.

05:58.210 --> 06:01.080
I did.
And then she showed up.

06:01.080 --> 06:03.120
[ Indistinct conversations,
telephone ringing ]

06:09.960 --> 06:13.380
I got an odd phone call
this morning.

06:13.380 --> 06:15.290
Are you holding
a DHS official?

06:15.290 --> 06:16.330
Who called you?

06:16.330 --> 06:17.750
Do you have grounds?

06:17.750 --> 06:18.670
I have questions.

06:18.670 --> 06:21.210
What questions?

06:21.210 --> 06:22.620
[ Sighs ]

06:22.620 --> 06:26.670
Cut him loose, please,
and start praying I can stop DHS

06:26.670 --> 06:28.710
from making you some
federal prosecutor's breakfast.

06:28.710 --> 06:30.000
I need more time.

06:30.000 --> 06:32.040
Look, you don't know
what's going on here.

06:32.040 --> 06:33.670
Then enlighten me.

06:35.330 --> 06:38.120
His name
is Craig Lindauer.

06:38.120 --> 06:39.750
His people had me
float this story

06:39.750 --> 06:41.880
that there weren't any survivors
from Thorn Beach.

06:41.880 --> 06:44.330
There were -- 47.

06:44.330 --> 06:46.670
They're keeping them
up at Camp Tamanowas.

06:46.670 --> 06:48.500
And I don't know
if they're safe.

06:48.500 --> 06:50.330
Wait.
The secret FEMA camp?

06:50.330 --> 06:52.080
I thought that whole thing
was a hoax.

06:54.670 --> 06:57.290
What is going on
up there?

06:57.290 --> 06:59.330
I don't know.

06:59.330 --> 07:00.960
That's why
I pulled him in.

07:00.960 --> 07:02.380
I want to talk to him.

07:05.170 --> 07:06.920
Mr. Lindauer.

07:06.920 --> 07:09.880
Vanessa Conway,
mayor of Port Canaan.

07:09.880 --> 07:11.000
It's a pleasure.

07:12.120 --> 07:15.880
I'm told you're operating
a detention facility

07:15.880 --> 07:17.330
in my backyard.

07:17.330 --> 07:20.380
Uh, yes, a temporary
housing situation,

07:20.380 --> 07:23.380
pending the resettlement
of our guests.

07:23.380 --> 07:26.710
Curious -- Where are your guests
visiting from?

07:26.710 --> 07:29.380
Unclear.

07:29.380 --> 07:33.460
Look, there are over 350,000
immigration detainees

07:33.460 --> 07:35.290
in this country
as we speak.

07:35.290 --> 07:36.750
This camp isn't
out of the ordinary.

07:36.750 --> 07:38.500
It is
if they're Americans.

07:38.500 --> 07:40.710
They all speak
American English,

07:40.710 --> 07:43.540
but we have no evidence that
supports American citizenship.

07:43.540 --> 07:45.960
None.

07:45.960 --> 07:49.460
I-I can see you're concerned,
and, uh, I want to help.

07:49.460 --> 07:52.500
It's a little unusual, but how
would you feel about a furlough?

07:52.500 --> 07:54.380
I could bring some of my people
into town

07:54.380 --> 07:55.580
for a supervised visit.

07:55.580 --> 07:57.080
We could even do it today.

07:57.080 --> 07:59.830
They get a little taste
of the promised land,

07:59.830 --> 08:03.420
and you get to put eyes on,
ease any fears you might have.

08:03.420 --> 08:05.580
I think that sounds
like a good idea,

08:05.580 --> 08:07.880
and I appreciate
your transparency,

08:07.880 --> 08:10.460
even if it was
an afterthought.

08:10.460 --> 08:11.710
Jude?

08:14.040 --> 08:15.830
[ Keys jingling ]

08:18.500 --> 08:20.210
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

08:23.210 --> 08:26.960
If anything
goes sideways today...

08:26.960 --> 08:28.670
I'm gonna
come after you.

08:28.670 --> 08:35.500
♪♪

08:35.500 --> 08:37.710
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

08:37.710 --> 08:45.290
♪♪

08:45.290 --> 08:47.670
Caleb: Hey, I know
you're worried about her.

08:47.670 --> 08:50.330
She'll be fine.

08:50.330 --> 08:53.420
You didn't see the way
they were looking at her.

08:53.420 --> 08:55.790
You didn't say anything,
did you?

08:55.790 --> 08:57.710
About what?

08:57.710 --> 08:59.920
That she came here
with an Apex.

08:59.920 --> 09:02.000
No.
Why would I do that?

09:04.330 --> 09:05.620
Hey.

09:05.620 --> 09:07.460
Hey.

09:07.460 --> 09:10.420
Leah's safe.
Nobody knows about her mother.

09:10.420 --> 09:12.080
You're overthinking this.

09:12.080 --> 09:13.380
I'm overthinking this?

09:13.380 --> 09:14.620
You're hoarding food

09:14.620 --> 09:17.330
because you think that
the guards may pull our meals.

09:17.330 --> 09:19.920
[ Scoffs ]

09:19.920 --> 09:24.080
Yeah, I guess this place is
making us both a little crazy.

09:24.080 --> 09:25.540
Yeah.

09:25.540 --> 09:26.580
Yeah.

09:28.750 --> 09:31.000
[ Door opens ]
Rebecca! We won!

09:31.000 --> 09:33.620
They called my name
and your name!

09:33.620 --> 09:35.210
Just come on!

09:36.750 --> 09:38.670
Bryce: Hannah.

09:38.670 --> 09:40.080
Peter.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.460
And John.

09:42.460 --> 09:44.710
Now, if your name wasn't called
this time, don't worry.

09:44.710 --> 09:46.080
Everyone will get a turn.

09:46.080 --> 09:48.080
We plan on making the day pass
a weekly occurrence

09:48.080 --> 09:49.880
-until you've been processed.
-Shh, shh, shh!

09:49.880 --> 09:52.960
If your name was called,
over to the bus ASAP.

09:52.960 --> 09:55.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:58.380 --> 10:00.170
Uh, sorry, we missed
the announcement.

10:00.170 --> 10:01.830
Day trip into town.

10:01.830 --> 10:03.920
You and Leah be on that bus
in 10, okay?

10:03.920 --> 10:05.620
I told you we won!

10:05.620 --> 10:06.880
Yes, you did.

10:06.880 --> 10:08.620
All right, go grab
something warm to put on.

10:08.620 --> 10:10.250
We got a bus to catch.
Go!

10:10.250 --> 10:11.750
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

10:11.750 --> 10:15.330
♪♪

10:15.330 --> 10:19.250
Maybe you should wait,
go on the next one.

10:19.250 --> 10:20.380
[ Door closes ]

10:20.380 --> 10:22.880
Babe, it's Leah's first day out
in weeks.

10:22.880 --> 10:24.420
She's gonna love this.

10:24.420 --> 10:27.000
I know, but I would
really feel better

10:27.000 --> 10:30.170
if we saw people go on today's
trip and come back safe.

10:30.170 --> 10:33.040
Let someone else
be guinea pigs.

10:33.040 --> 10:38.460
♪♪

10:38.460 --> 10:41.880
Okay.

10:41.880 --> 10:44.620
But you be safe,
all right?

10:44.620 --> 10:45.920
All right.

10:45.920 --> 10:52.960
♪♪

10:52.960 --> 10:56.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:56.580 --> 11:05.670
♪♪

11:05.670 --> 11:08.500
Reece: One...

11:08.500 --> 11:10.670
two...

11:10.670 --> 11:13.170
three...

11:13.170 --> 11:14.500
quatro.

11:14.500 --> 11:22.540
♪♪

11:22.540 --> 11:30.670
♪♪

11:30.670 --> 11:38.670
♪♪

11:38.670 --> 11:46.710
♪♪

11:50.580 --> 11:55.080
♪♪

11:55.080 --> 11:58.500
Bryce: Okay. We're a few miles
away from our destination.

11:58.500 --> 12:00.420
I think you all
understand our concern

12:00.420 --> 12:02.210
about your interactions
with townsfolk.

12:02.210 --> 12:05.120
For your safety,
the topics of how you arrived

12:05.120 --> 12:07.420
and where you came from
are off-limits.

12:07.420 --> 12:10.330
EJ and Roy will outfit each
of you with a tracking bracelet.

12:10.330 --> 12:12.330
Do not tamper
with these devices.

12:12.330 --> 12:14.170
Getting lost is understandable.

12:14.170 --> 12:15.790
Attempting to run is not.

12:15.790 --> 12:17.290
It's a violation of U.S. law.

12:17.290 --> 12:19.420
It puts your pending citizenship
in danger,

12:19.420 --> 12:22.420
and it will end day-pass
privileges for the whole camp.

12:22.420 --> 12:24.330
Okay, that's my speech.

12:24.330 --> 12:25.500
Enjoy yourselves.

12:28.620 --> 12:30.000
[ Sighs ]

12:34.420 --> 12:36.670
You need to take it easy.

12:36.670 --> 12:39.670
Lots of rest and fluids.

12:39.670 --> 12:42.420
And don't
exert yourself.

12:42.420 --> 12:44.920
I'll be back every two hours
to check on you.

12:44.920 --> 12:47.920
Who holds the keys here?

12:47.920 --> 12:50.710
-Um...
-Who's in charge?

12:50.710 --> 12:52.120
Agent Foster.

12:52.120 --> 12:54.170
But he's in town today.

12:54.170 --> 12:55.920
I need to talk to him.

12:55.920 --> 12:57.540
Sure, when he's back.

12:57.540 --> 12:59.540
But in the meantime,
you need to eat something

12:59.540 --> 13:00.960
and get your blood sugar up.

13:00.960 --> 13:02.750
Okay?
I'll go get you something.

13:04.880 --> 13:06.920
Are there markers?

13:06.920 --> 13:08.250
Excuse me?

13:10.500 --> 13:13.170
A writing implement
with a wide, fibrous tip.

13:15.880 --> 13:17.330
I'll see
what I can find.

13:17.330 --> 13:23.120
♪♪

13:23.120 --> 13:29.170
♪♪

13:29.170 --> 13:30.880
Nestor: Well, they didn't
give us any names,

13:30.880 --> 13:32.000
but with 10 of them coming,

13:32.000 --> 13:34.250
it's a 1 in 4 chance
that Hannah's among them.

13:34.250 --> 13:36.330
So you're gonna
be a guide.

13:36.330 --> 13:38.540
-What, like a tour guide?
-Yeah.

13:38.540 --> 13:40.250
Why? I-I don't know any
of the town's history.

13:40.250 --> 13:41.330
Well, why should you?

13:41.330 --> 13:43.000
You only lived here
your whole life.

13:43.000 --> 13:45.210
Look, I just want you to see
if you can find out

13:45.210 --> 13:46.920
what's going on
at that camp.

13:46.920 --> 13:50.920
Hey, let me
ask you something.

13:50.920 --> 13:54.380
She ever tell you anything
about herself?

13:54.380 --> 13:57.040
Uh, she's from Metolius, and she
had a messed-up childhood.

13:57.040 --> 13:59.250
That's about all I know.

13:59.250 --> 14:01.290
Okay.

14:01.290 --> 14:02.750
Am I getting paid
for this?

14:02.750 --> 14:04.580
No.

14:04.580 --> 14:06.830
-Hey.
-Hmm?

14:06.830 --> 14:08.580
Try to relax, okay?

14:08.580 --> 14:18.880
♪♪

14:18.880 --> 14:20.710
[ Brakes squeal ]

14:23.420 --> 14:24.750
Right on time.

14:24.750 --> 14:28.290
♪♪

14:28.290 --> 14:30.000
-Agent Foster?
-Yes, ma'am.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.380
-Vanessa Conway.
-Pleasure to meet you, ma'am.

14:32.380 --> 14:33.880
-Thanks for having us.
-Good to meet you, too.

14:33.880 --> 14:36.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:36.920 --> 14:39.040
That's Reece's daughter.

14:39.040 --> 14:41.170
Uh, I'm on kid duty.
You cover calls.

14:41.170 --> 14:42.420
Nestor: Copy that.

14:42.420 --> 14:44.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:44.420 --> 14:51.750
♪♪

14:51.750 --> 14:59.330
♪♪

14:59.330 --> 15:01.290
Jude: Well, well, well.

15:01.290 --> 15:03.250
If it isn't
the sweatshirt thief.

15:03.250 --> 15:04.880
You gave it to me.

15:04.880 --> 15:07.750
I don't know.
That doesn't sound like me.

15:07.750 --> 15:09.080
-Hi.
-Hi.

15:09.080 --> 15:10.620
-You're Jude, the sheriff.
-Mm-hmm.

15:10.620 --> 15:12.460
I'm Rebecca.

15:12.460 --> 15:14.080
I just want to say
thank you so much

15:14.080 --> 15:15.290
for that day
on the beach.

15:15.290 --> 15:17.710
Oh, I wish
I could've done more.

15:17.710 --> 15:19.420
I'm glad to see
that Dr. Forbin

15:19.420 --> 15:21.540
has worked her magic here
on Ms. Leah.

15:21.540 --> 15:24.170
She owes me a hoodie.

15:24.170 --> 15:25.620
[ Chuckles ]

15:25.620 --> 15:27.250
[ Seagulls crying ]

15:27.250 --> 15:29.210
You're here.

15:29.210 --> 15:31.080
How'd you know?

15:31.080 --> 15:33.210
Friends in high places.

15:33.210 --> 15:35.210
-You okay?
-Yeah.

15:35.210 --> 15:37.750
Been trying to phone,
like, nonstop.

15:37.750 --> 15:42.460
Yeah. Sorry.
It, uh, just stopped working.

15:42.460 --> 15:45.290
I like that you're worried,
though.

15:45.290 --> 15:46.960
Who said I was worried?

15:49.540 --> 15:51.670
[ Laughs ]

15:51.670 --> 15:52.920
[ Laughs ]

15:55.170 --> 15:58.040
[ Laughing ]
You're such a...

15:58.040 --> 15:59.960
[ Indistinct talking ]

15:59.960 --> 16:02.080
♪♪

16:02.080 --> 16:04.710
Well, since Leah and I here
have a history,

16:04.710 --> 16:07.710
I thought that, uh,
I could show you guys around.

16:07.710 --> 16:09.040
What do you think?

16:09.040 --> 16:10.880
-Yeah, sure.
-"Yeah, sure."

16:10.880 --> 16:12.790
Thanks for the vote
of confidence.

16:12.790 --> 16:14.250
I'm only
the sheriff here.

16:14.250 --> 16:15.500
Come on.

16:15.500 --> 16:20.210
♪♪

16:20.210 --> 16:22.460
So, how is everything
up there?

16:22.460 --> 16:23.830
-At the camp?
-Mm-hmm.

16:23.830 --> 16:25.830
It's fine.

16:25.830 --> 16:28.000
Are you sure
about that?

16:28.000 --> 16:29.380
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:29.380 --> 16:33.710
I've just seen, uh,
some pictures --

16:33.710 --> 16:37.290
electric fences
and extra guards and...

16:37.290 --> 16:40.540
Someone called for help
from in there.

16:40.540 --> 16:42.040
Oh.

16:42.040 --> 16:44.290
We're safe.
We're treated well.

16:44.290 --> 16:46.540
We've been given
a day out in town.

16:46.540 --> 16:48.620
This is amazing.

16:48.620 --> 16:52.170
I mean, people are just --
They're out.

16:52.170 --> 16:54.290
You know, it's...

16:54.290 --> 16:57.540
It's very different
than where we're from.

16:57.540 --> 16:59.420
Than when you're from.

16:59.420 --> 17:02.080
♪♪

17:02.080 --> 17:03.500
I know.

17:03.500 --> 17:07.920
♪♪

17:07.920 --> 17:10.170
I'm not supposed to
talk about that.

17:10.170 --> 17:13.790
♪♪

17:13.790 --> 17:16.420
[ Beeping ]

17:16.420 --> 17:25.920
♪♪

17:25.920 --> 17:35.620
♪♪

17:35.620 --> 17:45.170
♪♪

17:45.170 --> 17:47.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:47.830 --> 17:52.420
♪♪

17:52.420 --> 17:55.460
What does that
even mean?

17:55.460 --> 17:58.040
Jude: People here buy
a lot of crap they don't need.

17:58.040 --> 17:59.710
♪ Lower the curtain... ♪

17:59.710 --> 18:01.250
You have so much,
you know,

18:01.250 --> 18:03.120
clothing
and blankets and food

18:03.120 --> 18:05.500
and all the things that people
desperately needed

18:05.500 --> 18:06.920
where we came from.

18:06.920 --> 18:08.830
Hey.

18:08.830 --> 18:12.250
You don't need to be afraid
to talk to me.

18:12.250 --> 18:15.040
I know that there's something
going on up at that camp,

18:15.040 --> 18:17.170
and if -- if you're
being mistreated --

18:17.170 --> 18:19.710
No. No. It's --
It's not that.

18:19.710 --> 18:22.750
It's, um...

18:22.750 --> 18:25.830
I'm afraid for Leah.

18:25.830 --> 18:27.830
Well,
she's healthy now.

18:27.830 --> 18:31.500
That's the problem.
It's how she got healthy.

18:31.500 --> 18:33.500
Her mother.

18:33.500 --> 18:34.580
You know about that?

18:36.830 --> 18:39.880
Then you know
what she is.

18:39.880 --> 18:41.120
Yeah.

18:41.120 --> 18:44.830
♪♪

18:44.830 --> 18:48.460
If the people up at the camp,
if they found that out,

18:48.460 --> 18:51.000
they would
make Leah a target.

18:51.000 --> 18:52.960
But she hasn't
done anything.

18:52.960 --> 18:55.620
It doesn't matter.
It's the things that Apex did.

18:55.620 --> 18:58.210
Any affiliation, doesn't matter
how innocent you are,

18:58.210 --> 19:01.210
it marks you.

19:01.210 --> 19:03.000
So where is she?

19:05.080 --> 19:07.580
Leah's mother?

19:07.580 --> 19:08.920
I don't know.

19:08.920 --> 19:17.040
♪♪

19:17.040 --> 19:20.750
♪ Something shimmering
and white ♪

19:20.750 --> 19:23.710
I think
you'll like this one.

19:23.710 --> 19:26.620
♪ It leads you here ♪

19:26.620 --> 19:31.250
♪ Despite your destination ♪

19:31.250 --> 19:34.500
♪ Under the Milky Way tonight ♪

19:34.500 --> 19:36.500
[ Eerie music plays ]

19:36.500 --> 19:41.620
♪♪

19:41.620 --> 19:46.710
♪♪

19:46.710 --> 19:48.960
Hey.

19:48.960 --> 19:50.420
See anything you like?

19:50.420 --> 19:55.750
♪♪

19:59.460 --> 20:01.290
[ Beeping ]

20:01.290 --> 20:04.670
♪♪

20:04.670 --> 20:06.540
[ Rapid beeping ]

20:06.540 --> 20:14.540
♪♪

20:14.540 --> 20:15.790
[ Grunting ]

20:15.790 --> 20:21.790
♪♪

20:21.790 --> 20:28.040
♪♪

20:28.040 --> 20:30.540
Coming up on my left,
your right,

20:30.540 --> 20:32.920
is where I got my first
vandalism charge.

20:32.920 --> 20:36.000
A statue of...a guy

20:36.000 --> 20:39.250
was a popular spot to smoke pot
in 10th grade.

20:39.250 --> 20:41.500
Pot?
Marijuana.

20:41.500 --> 20:43.540
It's what 10th-grade screw-ups
use to get high.

20:43.540 --> 20:44.960
-What Ray said.
-Not my name.

20:44.960 --> 20:46.330
Anyway, I got caught

20:46.330 --> 20:48.290
spray-painting nipples
on this guy.

20:48.290 --> 20:52.500
I thought what Statue Guy
stood for is far more powerful

20:52.500 --> 20:55.920
if we remember he was once
just a man, like us.

20:55.920 --> 20:58.790
And what do we all have?

20:58.790 --> 21:01.000
What did
Abe Lincoln have?

21:01.000 --> 21:03.750
-Wow.
-Nipples, Ron.

21:05.620 --> 21:06.750
Nipples.

21:06.750 --> 21:10.040
♪♪

21:10.040 --> 21:12.380
Sometimes, they even wash up
on the shore, you know?

21:12.380 --> 21:14.710
[ Laughs ]

21:14.710 --> 21:16.420
-Yeah.
-Hey, guys.

21:16.420 --> 21:18.330
Let's try
to stick together.

21:18.330 --> 21:19.790
Sorry.

21:21.880 --> 21:23.580
[ Sighs ]

21:23.580 --> 21:27.750
You know,
this is like torture for me.

21:29.120 --> 21:31.210
Sorry to be a bother.

21:31.210 --> 21:32.620
No, it's...

21:32.620 --> 21:34.960
[ Sighs ]

21:34.960 --> 21:37.330
Look, I-I can't
walk next to you

21:37.330 --> 21:39.920
and not want
to hold your hand, and...

21:39.920 --> 21:41.460
knowing that you got to go back
to that camp

21:41.460 --> 21:43.880
at the end of the day,
it's...

21:43.880 --> 21:45.460
it's painful.

21:45.460 --> 21:50.920
♪♪

21:50.920 --> 21:52.540
We can't.

21:52.540 --> 21:58.120
♪♪

21:58.120 --> 21:59.670
Where are you going?

21:59.670 --> 22:02.170
♪♪

22:02.170 --> 22:03.120
Hey.

22:03.120 --> 22:05.000
♪♪

22:05.000 --> 22:06.210
Hey!

22:06.210 --> 22:07.540
Hey!

22:07.540 --> 22:08.620
[ Laughs ]

22:08.620 --> 22:10.460
[ Hannah
breathing heavily ]

22:10.460 --> 22:13.040
[ Both laugh ]

22:13.040 --> 22:21.040
♪♪

22:21.040 --> 22:22.960
[ Breathes deeply ]

22:22.960 --> 22:24.540
Why?
[ Breathing heavily ]

22:24.540 --> 22:34.670
♪♪

22:34.670 --> 22:44.500
♪♪

22:44.500 --> 22:46.290
Do you trust me?

22:46.290 --> 22:54.620
♪♪

22:54.620 --> 22:56.420
[ Breathing heavily ]

22:56.420 --> 23:06.040
♪♪

23:06.040 --> 23:07.330
[ Hannah laughs ]

23:07.330 --> 23:08.670
[ Motor running ]

23:08.670 --> 23:12.960
♪♪

23:12.960 --> 23:14.420
Hannah!

23:14.420 --> 23:16.620
Please don't be mad!
I'll meet you back at the bus!

23:16.620 --> 23:18.460
I'll be fine!

23:18.460 --> 23:20.330
♪♪

23:20.330 --> 23:22.210
Whoo!

23:23.830 --> 23:26.120
[ Indistinct talking ]

23:28.540 --> 23:30.790
Girl: Aah!
Mama!

23:30.790 --> 23:32.580
[ Laughs ]

23:35.500 --> 23:37.460
Hey.

23:37.460 --> 23:40.330
Sounds scary, but they're
having a good time.

23:40.330 --> 23:42.540
You ever been
on a swing?

23:42.540 --> 23:44.750
Miss Leah, you've never
been on a swing?

23:44.750 --> 23:46.540
That's unacceptable.

23:46.540 --> 23:47.960
It looks dangerous.

23:47.960 --> 23:49.790
Nonsense!

23:49.790 --> 23:52.000
You're in danger
of having fun, kid.

23:52.000 --> 23:53.380
Come on. Let's go.

23:53.380 --> 23:55.830
Watch out! [ Grunts ]

23:55.830 --> 23:58.540
All right.
Butt in the swing.

23:58.540 --> 24:00.790
♪♪

24:00.790 --> 24:02.250
Up.

24:02.250 --> 24:03.460
All right.

24:03.460 --> 24:05.790
There you go.
Wrap your paws around these.

24:05.790 --> 24:06.790
Hold on real tight.

24:06.790 --> 24:08.420
Now, when I let go,

24:08.420 --> 24:11.000
you're gonna reach out with
your feet as far as you can,

24:11.000 --> 24:13.080
just like these guys over here,
okay?

24:13.080 --> 24:15.620
And then when you're
coming back, bend your knees.

24:15.620 --> 24:17.120
[ Grunts ]

24:17.120 --> 24:18.330
Right!

24:18.330 --> 24:19.580
Reach out!

24:19.580 --> 24:21.210
Now bend 'em.
There you go.

24:21.210 --> 24:22.960
-[ Laughs ]
-Good!

24:22.960 --> 24:24.250
Bend your knees.

24:24.250 --> 24:25.750
-Yes!
-Reach out.

24:25.750 --> 24:27.080
You're a natural.

24:27.080 --> 24:29.040
-[ Laughs ]
-Good.

24:29.040 --> 24:30.500
-All right.
-Yay!

24:30.500 --> 24:31.620
You're on your own now.

24:31.620 --> 24:39.170
♪♪

24:39.170 --> 24:46.750
♪♪

24:46.750 --> 24:50.000
[ Indistinct talking, laughter ]

24:50.000 --> 24:55.670
♪♪

24:55.670 --> 25:01.620
♪♪

25:01.620 --> 25:03.460
What time is it?

25:03.460 --> 25:05.500
10 minutes later than
the last time you asked.

25:05.500 --> 25:06.960
Hey.

25:06.960 --> 25:09.580
Whales are on the wall,
just so you know.

25:09.580 --> 25:11.330
They're not
going anywhere.

25:11.330 --> 25:13.420
[ Seagulls crying ]

25:20.000 --> 25:22.000
I have to use the bathroom.

25:22.000 --> 25:23.620
All right.
We'll wait here.

25:28.250 --> 25:31.880
[ Door creaks, closes ]

25:31.880 --> 25:39.000
♪♪

25:39.000 --> 25:46.080
♪♪

25:46.080 --> 25:53.210
♪♪

25:53.210 --> 25:54.960
-Mama?
-Shh!

25:54.960 --> 26:00.710
♪♪

26:00.710 --> 26:06.290
♪♪

26:06.290 --> 26:08.580
-Mama!
-Hey, baby girl.

26:08.580 --> 26:10.540
[ Sighs ]

26:10.540 --> 26:12.500
♪♪

26:12.500 --> 26:13.710
[ Laughs ]

26:13.710 --> 26:18.790
♪♪

26:18.790 --> 26:20.120
Jude: Hey.

26:20.120 --> 26:22.420
♪♪

26:22.420 --> 26:23.080
[ Sighs ]

26:26.750 --> 26:30.290
♪♪

26:30.290 --> 26:31.960
You don't want
to do this.

26:31.960 --> 26:33.710
You don't know
what I want.

26:33.710 --> 26:37.620
♪♪

26:37.620 --> 26:38.750
Come here, kid.

26:38.750 --> 26:40.670
Let's do something
about that bracelet.

26:42.790 --> 26:45.540
All right.
Let me see.

26:45.540 --> 26:49.420
There you go.
All right.

26:49.420 --> 26:52.420
This is gonna feel a little icky
and cold, okay?

26:52.420 --> 26:55.080
But it's gonna help.

26:55.080 --> 26:57.290
♪♪

26:57.290 --> 26:59.210
Ready?
[ Inhales sharply ]

27:01.120 --> 27:03.580
You okay?

27:03.580 --> 27:06.080
Oh! Gee!
[ Chuckles ]

27:06.080 --> 27:07.750
All right.

27:07.750 --> 27:09.580
Come on, baby girl.

27:09.580 --> 27:11.880
♪♪

27:11.880 --> 27:13.670
[ Vehicle door opens ]

27:13.670 --> 27:20.250
♪♪

27:20.250 --> 27:22.500
Be careful.

27:22.500 --> 27:24.380
You be careful, too.

27:24.380 --> 27:26.830
♪♪

27:26.830 --> 27:27.710
[ Vehicle door opens ]

27:27.710 --> 27:29.040
[ Engine starts ]

27:29.040 --> 27:33.000
♪♪

27:33.000 --> 27:34.580
Leah?

27:34.580 --> 27:37.040
Leah!

27:37.040 --> 27:39.290
-Was that...
-Yes.

27:39.290 --> 27:40.460
-She's with her mother now.
-No.

27:40.460 --> 27:42.000
It's for the best.

27:42.000 --> 27:45.040
No, you have no idea
what you've just done.

27:45.040 --> 27:49.170
Hey.
You want Leah to be safe.

27:49.170 --> 27:51.460
I can't think of anybody
that can keep her safer

27:51.460 --> 27:53.170
than that woman
right there.

27:53.170 --> 27:56.170
Anyone that stands
between her and that kid

27:56.170 --> 27:58.290
is not long
for this world.

27:58.290 --> 28:00.460
Please.

28:00.460 --> 28:02.000
Let it go.

28:02.000 --> 28:04.920
♪♪

28:04.920 --> 28:06.540
[ Seagulls crying ]

28:06.540 --> 28:09.290
Marshall:
First boy to break your heart?

28:09.290 --> 28:11.830
Um, Micah.

28:11.830 --> 28:13.880
Only boy
to break my heart.

28:15.710 --> 28:18.000
Micah...

28:18.000 --> 28:19.380
We grew up
together.

28:19.380 --> 28:21.170
Our dads
were best friends.

28:21.170 --> 28:25.620
And when things
got really bad,

28:25.620 --> 28:27.750
um, his family
moved in with us.

28:27.750 --> 28:31.000
We shared everything --
beds, food.

28:31.000 --> 28:33.120
There wasn't enough food
half the time,

28:33.120 --> 28:34.750
and we thought
he'd disappear.

28:34.750 --> 28:35.750
He was so skinny.

28:35.750 --> 28:39.210
And then 'round 16,

28:39.210 --> 28:40.710
it was like, overnight,

28:40.710 --> 28:43.420
he just had these big,
broad shoulders and arms

28:43.420 --> 28:45.330
and facial hair.

28:45.330 --> 28:47.120
Suddenly,
there was Micah.

28:47.120 --> 28:49.380
Okay.
Yeah, I got the picture.

28:49.380 --> 28:57.380
♪♪

28:57.380 --> 29:05.380
♪♪

29:05.380 --> 29:09.750
Uh, so I guess
you grew up poor.

29:09.750 --> 29:12.670
Yeah.

29:12.670 --> 29:14.750
We don't have to
talk about that.

29:14.750 --> 29:16.210
We're having
such a good time.

29:16.210 --> 29:17.920
No, come on.

29:17.920 --> 29:20.040
I mean it.

29:20.040 --> 29:21.580
I want to know
about you.

29:21.580 --> 29:27.960
♪♪

29:27.960 --> 29:31.960
When we met
at Harborfest...

29:31.960 --> 29:34.080
I recognized you.

29:34.080 --> 29:37.290
♪♪

29:37.290 --> 29:41.120
Before I-I came
to Port Canaan...

29:43.580 --> 29:47.620
...someone gave me a locket
with your picture in it.

29:47.620 --> 29:50.580
They told me
to find you.

29:50.580 --> 29:53.920
They said you were a good man
and that you'd help me.

29:53.920 --> 29:57.210
♪♪

29:57.210 --> 30:00.580
Someone from Metolius
put my picture in a locket?

30:02.330 --> 30:04.170
Someone from Metolius...

30:06.960 --> 30:09.330
...in 2194.

30:09.330 --> 30:12.750
♪♪

30:12.750 --> 30:16.920
Me and those people
at that camp,

30:16.920 --> 30:20.210
we -- we came here

30:20.210 --> 30:22.330
to escape a war...

30:24.290 --> 30:25.750
...in the future.

30:28.120 --> 30:31.420
And this is the part where
you tell me you're joking

30:31.420 --> 30:33.420
and tell me
the real story?

30:33.420 --> 30:36.000
I know how it sounds.
[ Sighs ]

30:36.000 --> 30:38.000
That's why I didn't
say anything before.

30:38.000 --> 30:44.420
♪♪

30:44.420 --> 30:48.000
Okay, um...

30:48.000 --> 30:51.250
I mean,
what do I say to that?

30:54.790 --> 30:56.580
It's the truth,
Marshall.

30:56.580 --> 31:04.040
♪♪

31:04.040 --> 31:06.580
Mm.
What are you thinking?

31:06.580 --> 31:11.330
♪♪

31:11.330 --> 31:14.420
I was just thinking
that this conversation

31:14.420 --> 31:17.460
requires some whiskey.

31:17.460 --> 31:18.500
Ever had it?

31:18.500 --> 31:24.420
♪♪

31:24.420 --> 31:28.120
I'll hit the liquor store
down the beach.

31:28.120 --> 31:29.880
You're gonna love it.

31:29.880 --> 31:36.120
♪♪

31:36.120 --> 31:38.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:44.880 --> 31:46.210
Hey, what's going on?

31:46.210 --> 31:49.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:49.830 --> 31:51.460
You have to see this.

31:54.710 --> 32:00.380
♪♪

32:00.380 --> 32:06.170
♪♪

32:06.170 --> 32:08.250
You know
what that writing is?

32:11.500 --> 32:14.120
Yeah. I do.

32:19.500 --> 32:22.580
[ Upbeat rock music plays,
indistinct conversations ]

32:22.580 --> 32:25.040
♪♪

32:25.040 --> 32:26.500
What are you doing?

32:26.500 --> 32:28.380
You're supposed to be
with Hannah and the others.

32:28.380 --> 32:30.580
No. Tour's over.

32:30.580 --> 32:32.000
Okay.

32:32.000 --> 32:33.420
What'd you find out?

32:33.420 --> 32:36.540
That I should've gone to L.A.
with Claire.

32:36.540 --> 32:38.000
That's what I found out.

32:41.880 --> 32:43.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:43.830 --> 32:51.670
♪♪

32:51.670 --> 32:53.330
Young lady.

32:53.330 --> 32:55.500
You're too pretty
to be sad.

32:55.500 --> 33:00.670
♪♪

33:00.670 --> 33:05.750
♪♪

33:05.750 --> 33:07.290
Oh, my God.

33:07.290 --> 33:09.120
See something you like?

33:09.120 --> 33:11.460
I can cut you
a really good price.

33:11.460 --> 33:12.880
Depression discount.

33:12.880 --> 33:14.420
This is my locket.

33:14.420 --> 33:16.170
10 bucks, it's yours.

33:16.170 --> 33:17.920
No, no, I lost this
in the water.

33:17.920 --> 33:19.120
Where did you find it?

33:19.120 --> 33:21.580
Lady, if you're not gonna
buy it, put it down.

33:21.580 --> 33:23.620
I'm not buying my own locket
from you,

33:23.620 --> 33:25.040
and I don't have
any money.

33:25.040 --> 33:28.040
Uh, hey! Help!

33:28.040 --> 33:29.960
She stole from me!

33:29.960 --> 33:31.880
♪♪

33:31.880 --> 33:33.620
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

33:33.620 --> 33:35.290
Hold on to her!
She stole from me!

33:35.290 --> 33:36.830
He's trying to sell it,
but it's mine.

33:36.830 --> 33:38.710
I-I lost it when we
washed up on the...

33:38.710 --> 33:40.250
Be quiet.

33:40.250 --> 33:42.000
Here.

33:42.000 --> 33:43.830
We gave you
an easy set of rules.

33:43.830 --> 33:45.960
I guess you're just not
that interested in citizenship.

33:45.960 --> 33:48.290
Hey, are you guys
from the refugee camp?

33:48.290 --> 33:50.080
Didn't we take care
of your thing? Piss off.

33:50.080 --> 33:52.210
EJ.
Back to the bus.

33:55.830 --> 33:57.880
My apologies, sir.

33:57.880 --> 33:58.710
-Wait.
-Hannah.

33:58.710 --> 34:00.380
No, wait. Roy.

34:00.380 --> 34:03.210
Wait. That guy has my locket,
the one I lost,

34:03.210 --> 34:04.710
the only thing I brought
from home.

34:04.710 --> 34:06.080
Remember?
Roy!

34:06.080 --> 34:07.920
We have to go back.

34:07.920 --> 34:10.250
Hannah,
I don't care.

34:10.250 --> 34:12.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

34:12.580 --> 34:17.330
♪♪

34:17.330 --> 34:19.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

34:19.830 --> 34:25.620
♪♪

34:25.620 --> 34:28.170
Roy.

34:28.170 --> 34:30.040
Please talk to me.

34:30.040 --> 34:36.580
♪♪

34:36.580 --> 34:43.420
♪♪

34:43.420 --> 34:45.580
Yes, sir.

34:45.580 --> 34:47.330
Understood.

34:47.330 --> 34:50.330
[ Sighs ]

34:50.330 --> 34:53.620
We're short one
on the head count.

34:53.620 --> 34:55.460
HQ's on it.

34:55.460 --> 34:57.120
Our orders
are to take these back.

34:57.120 --> 34:59.170
They're sending another unit
for the missing one.

34:59.170 --> 35:01.620
How'd they know?
I just finished the head count.

35:01.620 --> 35:04.040
♪♪

35:04.040 --> 35:05.790
We've got our orders.

35:05.790 --> 35:11.170
♪♪

35:11.170 --> 35:12.880
[ Indistinct conversations ]

35:12.880 --> 35:17.710
♪♪

35:17.710 --> 35:18.960
What's wrong?

35:18.960 --> 35:27.920
♪♪

35:27.920 --> 35:36.830
♪♪

35:36.830 --> 35:39.420
[ Beeping, whirring ]

35:39.420 --> 35:40.710
Move in.

35:40.710 --> 35:44.710
♪♪

35:44.710 --> 35:46.500
[ Paper rustling ]

35:46.500 --> 35:50.580
♪♪

35:50.580 --> 35:52.080
Do you want
to play a game?

35:52.080 --> 35:53.580
-Yeah.
-[ Laughs ]

35:53.580 --> 35:54.920
Here's the game.

35:54.920 --> 35:57.960
I want you to find
a town on the map,

35:57.960 --> 35:59.710
and based on
the town's name,

35:59.710 --> 36:01.960
I want you to guess
what it's like,

36:01.960 --> 36:03.580
and should we
live there?

36:03.580 --> 36:07.250
♪♪

36:07.250 --> 36:10.750
There's a town
called Square "Butt".

36:10.750 --> 36:12.460
[ Both laugh ]

36:12.460 --> 36:22.250
♪♪

36:22.250 --> 36:24.960
[ Static,
high-pitched whirring ]

36:24.960 --> 36:33.960
♪♪

36:33.960 --> 36:36.080
Mama? What's wrong?

36:36.080 --> 36:37.540
[ Static, whirring continue ]

36:37.540 --> 36:45.880
♪♪

36:45.880 --> 36:47.120
[ Keys jingle ]

36:47.120 --> 36:48.460
Come on. Let's go.

36:48.460 --> 36:49.790
Come on.

36:49.790 --> 36:51.920
♪♪

36:51.920 --> 36:53.170
[ Car alarm chirps ]

36:54.540 --> 36:56.080
Belt on.

36:56.080 --> 37:01.000
♪♪

37:01.000 --> 37:03.790
[ Vehicle door closes,
engine starts ]

37:03.790 --> 37:05.710
[ Tires squeal ]

37:09.580 --> 37:15.750
♪♪

37:15.750 --> 37:21.880
♪♪

37:21.880 --> 37:23.170
You seen this?

37:27.540 --> 37:29.000
[ Sighs ]

37:29.000 --> 37:30.080
Great.

37:32.750 --> 37:36.210
What's wrong?

37:36.210 --> 37:39.080
We missed something
today.

37:39.080 --> 37:41.790
What do you mean?

37:41.790 --> 37:43.920
You sent the kid off
with her mom,

37:43.920 --> 37:45.710
got one over on Lindauer.

37:45.710 --> 37:47.210
It's a good day.

37:47.210 --> 37:53.330
♪♪

37:53.330 --> 37:55.250
No.

37:55.250 --> 37:56.830
It was too easy.

37:56.830 --> 37:58.880
♪♪

37:58.880 --> 38:01.250
[ Engine revs ]

38:01.250 --> 38:03.670
He's been five moves
ahead of us.

38:03.670 --> 38:07.790
♪♪

38:07.790 --> 38:10.380
[ Engine revving ]

38:10.380 --> 38:12.750
♪♪

38:12.750 --> 38:14.250
[ Knock on door ]

38:14.250 --> 38:17.170
[ Door opens ]

38:17.170 --> 38:19.620
-Hello.
-Can I come in?

38:19.620 --> 38:22.830
♪♪

38:22.830 --> 38:24.620
[ Insects chirping ]

38:28.750 --> 38:31.250
[ Door closes ]

38:31.250 --> 38:37.920
♪♪

38:37.920 --> 38:44.790
♪♪

38:44.790 --> 38:47.540
How can you write
in Apex?

38:47.540 --> 38:55.830
♪♪

38:55.830 --> 38:58.080
I didn't have a choice.

38:58.080 --> 39:01.040
♪♪

39:01.040 --> 39:03.290
You belong to them.

39:03.290 --> 39:11.710
♪♪

39:11.710 --> 39:13.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

39:13.250 --> 39:14.710
Sir?

39:19.250 --> 39:23.620
I wanted to apologize again
for my colleague, and, uh...

39:25.290 --> 39:28.620
Well, I wa-- I was wondering
if you still had that, uh...

39:28.620 --> 39:29.380
Oh.

39:29.380 --> 39:30.920
Uh...

39:34.790 --> 39:36.830
25 bucks.

39:36.830 --> 39:38.080
Sure.

39:38.080 --> 39:41.170
♪♪

39:41.170 --> 39:43.500
This is
a romantic gesture.

39:43.500 --> 39:48.620
♪♪

39:48.620 --> 39:54.000
♪♪

39:54.000 --> 39:56.420
Have a good one.

39:56.420 --> 39:59.380
You might not want
to open that, Romeo.

39:59.380 --> 40:06.330
♪♪

40:06.330 --> 40:13.210
♪♪

40:13.210 --> 40:20.170
♪♪

40:20.170 --> 40:22.500
[ Engine revving ]

40:22.500 --> 40:29.920
♪♪

40:29.920 --> 40:37.540
♪♪

40:37.540 --> 40:39.080
[ Tires screeching ]

40:39.080 --> 40:43.120
♪♪

40:43.120 --> 40:44.750
-Aah!
-[ Grunts ]

40:44.750 --> 40:47.880
[ Tires screeching ]

40:47.880 --> 40:49.170
[ Breathing heavily ]

40:49.170 --> 40:51.580
[ Metal clinking ]

40:51.580 --> 40:52.420
Uh!

40:54.580 --> 40:55.580
Leah: Mom?

40:55.580 --> 40:57.620
[ Grunting ]

40:57.620 --> 41:01.960
♪♪

41:01.960 --> 41:03.210
[ Whimpering ]

41:03.210 --> 41:04.710
Ow! Mama!

41:04.710 --> 41:06.330
[ Grunting ]

41:06.330 --> 41:08.500
[ Electricity crackling ]
Aah!

41:08.500 --> 41:09.790
Leah: Mama!

41:09.790 --> 41:12.210
-No!
-Mama!

41:12.210 --> 41:14.500
[ Crackling continues ]
[ Grunts ]

41:14.500 --> 41:16.790
Mama!

41:16.790 --> 41:19.170
[ Slow, dramatic music plays,
slow-motion moaning ]

41:21.830 --> 41:23.620
[ Echoing ] Mama!

41:23.620 --> 41:30.620
♪♪

41:30.620 --> 41:33.290
Mama!

41:33.290 --> 41:39.460
♪♪

41:39.460 --> 41:41.920
Mama!

41:41.920 --> 41:51.250
♪♪

41:51.250 --> 41:53.210
Mama!

41:53.210 --> 41:58.830
♪♪

41:58.830 --> 42:04.830
♪♪

42:04.830 --> 42:06.080
Target acquired.

42:06.080 --> 42:14.330
♪♪

42:18.170 --> 42:27.540
♪♪

42:27.540 --> 42:36.710
♪♪

